The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 December is 11,399 (1,319.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 December, there were 1,054 new confirmed cases (122.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 December, there were 593 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 78% (461 extra cases).
